 distance towards her.<P>My Warrior carved him and his group up with Warrior's Swing.<P>It's a strange fact, but the DoL is actually one of the weakest creatures in the game comparative to your hero  <IMG SRC="http://www.larian.com/ubb/smile.gif"></FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">progm_test</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">demon of lies.... he is just a body with flesh after all... <BR>I. <BR>------------------------------------------------------<BR>1. shadow potions<BR>2. freeze spell<BR>3. lightning, fire, or attack with a weapon then shadow again<BR>------------------------------------------------------<BR>or<P>II. <BR>------------------------------------------------------<BR>1. polymorphy to turn him into a harmless creature<BR>2. do what ever you want because he won't fight back<BR>------------------------------------------------------<P>the combination of shadow potions and scorpion traps were too powerful<BR>----&gt; <BR>cause the game was too easy to play.... or because i played a normal game... </FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtexture.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Setharmon</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Originally posted by cfcdicko:<BR><I>Thandui  i know how u feel i have spent the last week trying to find out what i do after i kill the demon of lies because i thiught that there would be a ending sequence or something. I used 2 lvl 5 death scorpions to kill him and his mates while i hid with shadows.<P>I have heard however that if u do it again use metorstrike because it is effective.<P>craig</I><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Hey... I seem to remember something about using scorps to kill him.<BR>There have been posts about that. It's just becouse you don't finish it "yourself" that you don't get the cut scene.